'''Samantha Ruth Prabhu''' is an Indian film actress and model who appears in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Tamil language|Tamil]] films. Born to [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Malayalam language|Malayali]] parents, Samantha was brought up in [[Chennai]] and pursued a career in modeling during her late teens. Despite signing up to [[Ravi Varman]]'s ''[[Moscowin Kavery]]'' in 2007, her first release happened to be the critically acclaimed 2010 [[Telugu language|Telugu]] [[romance film]], ''[[Ye Maaya Chesave]]'', directed by [[Gautham Menon]].  She has then later appeared in critically acclaimed and commercially successful Telugu movies like ''[[Brindavanam]]'' and ''[[Dookudu]]''.

== Early life and family ==
Born on April 28, 1987 to a [[Malayali]] mother and a [[Telugu people|Telugu]] father,her mother tongues are [[Telugu Language|Telugu]] and  [[Malayalam]].Samantha was brought up in [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]] as the youngest child of the family to Prabhu and Ninette and two elder brothers Jonathan and David, whilst becoming fluent in the [[Tamil language]].<ref name="tamilsam">{{cite web|author=Shankar, Settu|year=2008|title=Samantha Christens herself Yashodha!|publisher=OneIndia|accessdate=2008-08-05|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/exclusive/2008/samantha-name-yashoda-250808.html}}</ref> She was brought up speaking Tamil and English at home.<ref name="tamilsam2">{{cite news|author=Chowdury, Sunita Y|year=2010|title=Poised on the edge|work=The Hindu |location=India|accessdate=2010-03-01|url=http://beta.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article124253.ece|date=2010-03-01}}</ref><ref name="tamilsam3">{{cite news|author=Prakash, B|title=It wasn<U+2019>t a liplock really: Samantha|work=Times of India |location=India|accessdate=2010-03-07|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/It-wasnt-a-liplock-really-Samantha/articleshow/5651555.cms|date=2010-03-07}}</ref> As part of her education, Samantha completed her schooling from Holy Angels Anglo-Indian Higher Secondary School, T. Nagar. She also has a degree in [[commerce]] at [[Stella Maris College, Chennai]].<ref name="tamilsam2"/>

== Career ==
Despite signing up for three Tamil films in quick succession, Samantha's first  Boy friend Name Pratap.R This is a bilingual film, created much anticipation prior to release, primarily due to the first-time-collaboration between Menon and composer [[A. R. Rahman]].<ref name="anti">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2010|title=Audio released, confirms release on Feb&nbsp;19!|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=2010-02-04|url=http://sify.com/movies/telugu/fullstory.php?id=14930062&cid=2364}}</ref> The actress was signed up for the project in mid August 2009 and completed schedules across India and the United States for the film which released in February 26, 2010.<ref name="signup">{{cite news|author=TNN|title=Big break for Samantha|work=Times of India |location=India|accessdate=2009-09-24|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Big-break-for-Samantha/articleshow/5046713.cms|date=2009-09-24}}</ref> The film portrays Samantha as the lead character of ''Jessie'', which was also the working title of the film; a [[Malayali]] Christian girl living in [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]], whom the male protagonist, played by [[Naga Chaitanya]] falls in love with. Upon release, Samantha received very positive reviews for her portrayal, with the film also garnering much critical acclaim.<ref name="sifyreview">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2010|title=Ye Maaya Chesave|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=2010-02-26|url=http://sify.com/movies/telugu/review.php?id=14933284&ctid=5&cid=2430}}</ref> Critics at [[Sify]] claimed that Samantha was the "scene-stealer" and her beauty "is alluring" adding that "she was the girl to watch out for".<ref name="sifyreview"/> Jeevi, from the Idlebrain reviews site, cited that "Samantha<U+2019>s debut is one of the best heroine debuts in Telugu cinema" and that her "minute expressions she gave spoke volumes about her", whilst labelling the film as a "classic". Samantha, alongside her co-star, Naga Chaitanya, also appeared in a guest appearance in the Tamil version of the film.<ref name="idlereview">{{cite web|author=Jeevi|year=2010|title=Ye Maya Chesave|publisher=Idlebrain|accessdate=2010-02-26|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-yemayachesave.html}}</ref> Both films emerged as grand successes in Tamil and Telugu respectively, propelling Samantha to sign bigger projects.<ref name="interviewrediff">{{cite web|author=Warrier, Shobha|year=2010|title=Meet Yeh Maya Chesave's Jessie|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=2010-04-30|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/apr/30/slide-show-1-south-interview-with-samantha.htm#contentTop}}</ref> She followed up her collaborations with Gautham Menon and A. R. Rahman by appearing in the music video for the [[World Classical Tamil Conference 2010]] promotional song, ''[[Semmozhiyaana Tamizh Mozhiyaam]]'', which Menon directed and Rahman composed.

Samantha's next release was the Sathya Jyothi-produced romantic drama, ''[[Baana Kaathadi]]'', opposite [[Adharvaa Murali|Adharvaa]], which was actually the third Tamil film signed by her, but released first due to the delay of the other two projects.<ref name="samsban">{{cite web|author=|year=2009|title=<U+2018>Baana Kaathadi<U+2019> getting ready to fly|publisher=Indiaglitz|accessdate=2009-07-01|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/47985.html}}</ref><ref name="thehindu1">{{cite news|author=Ashok Kumar, S. R.|year=2010|title=My First Break: Samantha|work=The Hindu |location=India|accessdate=2010-08-22|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article582130.ece|date=2010-08-19}}</ref> Following agreeing terms in early 2009, the film continued shoot for a year and after several postponements finally released in August 2010 to positive responses.<ref name="thehindu1"/><ref>{{cite web|author=|year=2010|title=Friday Fury- August&nbsp;6|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=2010-08-06|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14952315}}</ref> In the film, Samantha plays a student of the [[National Institute of Fashion Technology]] (NIFT), the first such role in [[Tamil cinema]].<ref name="samstud">{{cite news|author=Raghavan, Nikhil|title=Another scorcher |work=The Hindu |location=India|accessdate=2009-03-27|url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2009/03/27/stories/2009032750220900.htm|date=2009-03-27}}</ref> Her next release, was [[Ravi Varman]]'s ''[[Moscowin Kavery]]'', initially her very first acting assignment, which began in August 2007, with Samantha, then briefly known as Yasodha, joining the team later in the year.<ref name="ravivarm">{{cite web|author=|year=2007|title=Ravi Varman directs an Oscar Films production|publisher=Cinesouth|accessdate=2007-08-27|url=http://www.cinesouth.com/masala/hotnews/new/27082007-4.shtml}}</ref> The film introduced a host of new actors, with music carried out by [[Thaman]], then making his debut in music composing. In an interview, much prior to release in 2008, Ravi Varman mentioned that he had decided that Samantha would be the lead actress for his film within three minutes after viewing one of her commercial assignments.<ref name="ravivarman">{{cite web|author=|year=2008|title=Ravi Varman Interview|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=2008-06-28|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/features/Interviews/interview-5/ravi-varman/index.html}}</ref> In the interview, he went on to describe her as an actress with "intelligence" and "potential", whilst drawing comparisons with noted actress, [[Revathi]].<ref name="ravivarman"/> However, due to Ravi Varman's date conflicts with his projects as a cinematographer, the film languished in [[development hell]], eventually releasing in August 2010.<ref name="aascardelayn">{{cite web|author=|year=2009|title=Aascar<U+2019>s back-to-back releases|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=2009-11-14|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-09-02/leelai-moscowin-kaveri-14-11-09.html}}</ref> The film gained unanimously poor reviews from critics,<ref name="mkreview2">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2010|title=Movie Review: Moscowin Kaveri |publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=2010-08-27|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14954792&ctid=5&cid=2429}}</ref> however Samantha's performance was labelled as one of the sole highlights that the film offered.<ref name="mkreview1">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra|year=2010|title=Moscowin Kaveri is beautiful nonsense|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=2010-08-27|url=http://movies.rediff.com/review/2010/aug/27/south-tamil-review-moscowin-kaveri.htm}}</ref> Samantha, during the making of the last three releases, had also signed up for the [[Narain (actor)|Narain]] starrer, ''Pookada Ravi'' in August 2008 to play the lead role of a modern girl.<ref name="pookadasignn">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2008|title=Samantha is Narain's heroine!|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=2008-08-24|url=http://sify.in/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14744707&cid=14490563}}</ref> Despite the film continuing schedules at regular intervals, the film was stalled throughout 2009 and is unlikely to be released.<ref name="pookada">{{cite news|author=Prasad, G.|title=Image booster for Narain |work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=2009-02-15|url=http://www.hindu.com/2009/02/15/stories/2009021557590200.htm|date=2009-02-15|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> Samantha went onto feature in [[Vamsi Paidipally]]'s ''[[Brindaavanam]]'' in which she had a supporting role alongside [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.|NTR Jr]] and [[Kajal Aggarwal]].<ref name="samntr">{{cite web|author=|year=2010|title=Samantha in NTR's Brindavanam|work=Times of India |location=India|accessdate=2010-02-15|url=http://timesofindia.hotklix.com/Hotklix/link/Entertainment/Movies/Samantha-in-NTR-s-Brindavanam-Telugu-Cinema-News}}</ref> Her role of Indu was well received despite being shorter in screen time than her previous roles and the film became her second successful Telugu film.<ref name="brindahit">{{cite news|author=|year=2010|title=NTR's Brindavanam creates waves at box-office|work=OneIndia.com|accessdate=2010-10-16|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/telugu/top-stories/2010/brindavanam-ntr-waves-box-office-161010.html}}</ref> 

In 2011, Samantha made a guest appearance as a mentally ill patient in Gautham Menon's ''[[Nadunisi Naaygal]]'', before featuring in the big budget Telugu film, ''[[Dookudu]]'', along side [[Mahesh Babu]]. The film opened to positive review with critics from [[CNN-IBN]] labelling the film as "a treat for Mahesh's fans", adding that Samantha "looks good in song sequences"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/telugu-review-dookudu-is-a-mahesh-babu-film/187437-8-69.html|title=Telugu Review: 'Dookudu' an out and out Mahesh Babu film|publisher=CNN-IBN|accessdate= Sep 25, 2011}}</ref> ''[[The Times Of India]]'' also praised the film mentioning that "Samantha looks beautiful and has done a great job, though her role as Prashanthi isn't too lengthy".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/telugu/Dookudu/moviereview/10093005.cms|title=Dookudu|publisher=Times Of India|accessdate=Sep 24, 2011}}</ref> The film took the largest ever opening for a [[Telugu cinema|Telugu film]] and grossed {{INR}}12.58 crores on the first day of its release,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/71379.html|title=Dookudu's first day gross: Rs. 12.58 cr.|publisher=IndiaGlitz}}</ref> on its way to becoming the highest grossing Telugu film of the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/71569.html|title=Dookudu's unbelievable 7-day gross: Rs. 50.07 cr.|publisher=IndiaGlitz}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://idlebrain.com/trade/dookudu-milliondollarsusa.html|title=Mahesh<U+2019>s Million US Dollar Dookudu|publisher=idlebrain}}</ref> 

Samantha is currently working on more than half-a-dozen projects.<ref name="sify1">http://www.sify.com/movies/samantha-to-reign-tollywood-news-news-mcgoJDjjfeb.html</ref> She is filming for [[S. S. Rajamouli]]'s live action project ''[[Eega]]'',<ref name="sammbb">{{cite news|author=Pillai, Sreedhar|title=Samantha's walk in the clouds|work=Times of India |location=India|accessdate=2010-04-16|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/Samanthas-walk-in-the-clouds/articleshow/5811462.cms|date=2010-04-16}}</ref> as well as for [[Gautham Menon]]'s trilingual project,<ref>{{cite web|title= Gautham creates history with a trilingual |url= http://www.sify.com/movies/gautham-creates-history-with-a-trilingual-news-tamil-ljoloBjijei.html |publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=11 July 2011}}</ref> playing the female lead in all three languages<U+2014>Tamil, Telugu and Hindi<U+2014>and shooting all scenes thrice with different co-actors.<ref>http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/tollywood/samantha<U+2019>s-new-challenge-489</ref> She has also signed for the big budget films ''[[Yevadu]]'' to be directed by [[Vamsi Paidipally]], co-starring [[Ram Charan Tej]] and ''[[Seethamma Vakitlo Sirimalle Chettu]]'' that features [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] and [[Mahesh Babu]] in the lead.<ref name="sify1"/> Her other upcoming projects in Telugu include ''[[Autonagar Surya]]'' under the direction of [[Deva Katta]] and [[Nandini Reddy]]'s next co-starring [[Siddharth (actor)|Siddharth]].<ref name="sify1"/> Moreover, she has been chosen by [[Mani Ratnam]] to portray the female lead in his next directorial ''[[Kadal (film)|Kadal]]''.<ref name="sify1"/>

